	('A-rZzfBbIGwWlxGKaJaTW', 'Ethereal Monarch Part 1', 'https://utfs.io/f/a07eda68-9ae6-435b-aca2-03119492b782-ska6rd.webp', '<p>The Origins of the Monarch<br>\nThe Ethereal Monarch was not born of mortal flesh but was a being of pure chakra, a manifestation of light and celestial power. It is said that the Monarch descended from the stars, arriving in Seichi during an era where the boundaries between the human world and the ethereal plane were thin. This Monarch wielded powers over light and darkness, the very forces that shaped the heavens themselves. The people of Seichi, awed by the brilliance and ethereal beauty of this being, revered them as a divine ruler, a guide who could illuminate the path to harmony between the mortal and spiritual realms.</p>\n\n<p>Rule Over the Celestial Throne<br>\nThe Monarch established their throne in the Sky Palace, a floating citadel surrounded by clouds and bathed in eternal twilight. From this celestial fortress, the Monarch governed both the physical and spiritual worlds. Their reign was marked by a golden age where the shinobi clans of Seichi flourished, learning to harness the power of light and shadow under the Monarch’s guidance. Peace and prosperity reigned, as the Monarch could see into the hearts of both men and spirits, bringing balance to all things.</p>\n\n<p>The Ethereal Monarch was not just a ruler but a protector, wielding the power of light to defend Seichi from dark entities and malevolent spirits that sought to breach the mortal realm. Tales tell of the Monarch raising their radiant hand, banishing entire armies of shadow with a single gesture.</p>\n\n<p>The Betrayal and Fall<br>\nHowever, such power inspired both awe and envy. A faction of power-hungry shinobi, believing that the Monarch’s influence hindered their rise to dominance, conspired to overthrow them. In a carefully orchestrated act of treachery, these conspirators invited dark forces into Seichi, hoping to siphon the Monarch\'s ethereal power.</p>\n\