	('k5g8ZbAT07pBlughQ-9RN', '[Path of Crimson] [Part III: Chains of Deception]', 'https://utfs.io/f/Hzww9EQvYURJEb4bwCLfKL5D7TAFe29bymSaPCIQ846MdzGg', '<center>\n<img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/zTrBw5TZ/Dusk-Avamation.webp\" alt=\"Dusk Avamation\"><br><br>\n\n<em>There\'s something wrong.</em><br><br>\n\n<em>The moment you step onto Wake Island, you feel it. The air is heavy, thick with the lingering scent of burned wood, but it’s more than that. It’s the silence. The way the ocean barely stirs against the docks. The way the distant embers on the mainland still glow, flickering like open wounds across the land.</em><br><br>\n\nAnd then there’s Dusk.<br><br>\n\nHe stands where he always does, near the island’s edge, his golden scarf resting against his shoulders instead of shifting with the wind. He doesn’t greet you with his usual smirk. He doesn’t say anything at all—not at first. When he finally does speak, it’s slower. Measured. Less like an old friend and more like someone choosing their words carefully.<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color:orange; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.2em;\">“It’s worse than I expected.”</span><br><br>\n\nHis gaze doesn’t leave the horizon. Even as he gestures toward the burned parchment on the nearby table, his fingers move almost mechanically, without the usual casual confidence.<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color:orange; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.2em;\">“The Maw isn’t just raiding anymore. They’re following a pattern. Marking sites. The Ember Trail was only the beginning.”</span><br><br>\n\nOn the map, two locations are circled in deep red ink. His hand lingers over them for a moment longer than necessary.<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color:orange; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.2em;\">“If they finish what they’ve started, we’re out of time. We need to act first.”</span><br><br>\n\nAnd then—finally—he looks at you. But something is missing.<br><br>\n\nThe usual sharp glint in his eyes isn’t there. His expression is neutral, his posture stiff, too still.<br><br>\n\nFor the first time since you met him, Dusk looks like he’s waiting. Not just for your answer, but for your reaction.<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color:orange; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.2em;\">“Destroy their operations. Take anything they were using. If they’re preparing something bigger, I want to know what it is.”</span><br><br>\n\nHis voice is steady, but there’s something beneath it. Not doubt. Not hesitation. Just… calculation.<br><br>\n\nAnd then, softer—<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color:orange; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.2em;\">“…And don’t hesitate. If you run into resistance, you know what to do.”</span><br><br>\n\nThat, at least, sounds like him. But somehow, it makes everything else feel even stranger.<br><br>\n\nHe hands you the map, his fingers brushing against yours for just a second longer than they should. It’s barely noticeable. But when he pulls away, he does it just a little too deliberately.<br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color:orange; font-weight:bold; font-size:1.2em;\">“Go. We don’t have time to waste.”</span><br><br>\n\nAnd with that, he turns back to the horizon, as if dismissing the conversation entirely. But for the first time, you’re not sure if he’s watching the burning sky—<br><br>\n\n—or making sure you’re leaving.\n</center>\n', NULL, 'D', 1, NULL, 'event', '{\"reward\": {\"reward_exp\": 0, \"reward_rank\": \"NONE\", \"reward_items\": [\"pwUdcxKy1_NzuN4matHOT\"], \"reward_money\": 0, \"reward_badges\": [\"zfndA4-zQqAmSzFvg22dD\"], \"reward_jutsus\": [], \"reward_tokens\": 0, \"reward_prestige\": 0, \"reward_clanpoints\": 0}, \"objectives\": [{\"id\": \"N5liF4AVJkxtTwbUJ_Pgg\", \"task\": \"collect_item\", \"image\": \"https://utfs.io/f/Hzww9EQvYURJdYVkZ3P62PI3ciLaYzgVX8FopBADxSrGmvQl\", \"sector\": 222, \"latitude\": 9, \"attackers\": [\"o5bvA2fo9QHDDw-t6hIXv\"], \"completed\": 0, \"item_name\": \"Blackened Map\", \"longitude\": 5, \"reward_exp\": 0, \"description\": \"\", \"reward_rank\": \"NONE\", \"hideLocation\": true, \