	('ObwK_ZLfWA3Oov-cfvMWJ', 'The Path to Tsukimori', 'https://utfs.io/f/52cba880-b1b1-41a1-816a-baffa62229d0-ajhq0g.webp', 'Greetings, young shinobi. The village of Tsukimori, forged in the heart of the Fireheart Forest, holds many secrets within its tranquil boundaries.Its history is woven with mystical encounters and deep connections to the moon, earth and its flora. To truly understand its origins, you must walk the path their ancestors once took. Join me in retracing these pivotal events and uncover the rich history of this revered land.Begin your journey at Fireheart Forest. <br><br>\n\nContinue to the Ironwood Forest, where the settlers encountered the sturdy and resilient spirits of the forest, who shared their wisdom and strength.<br><br>\n\nMake your way to Wildwonder Forest, a place of untamed beauty and mystery, where the settlers discovered the playful and curious spirits of the forest, who shared the mysteries and wonders of the forest with them.<br><br>\n\nNext, proceed to the Grey Hills. Known for their strategic high ground and valuable minerals, these hills became a site of contention. Oiwa, the vengeful spirit, watches over these lands, a testament to their ancient and mystical importance.<br><br>\n\nFinally make your way to Deadwood Hillside, a crucial site where Junko was attacked by the Hideki Rebels and later were saved and healed by Terriator.<br><br>\n', 'Congratulations, shinobi! You\'ve completed your mission in Tsukimori, uncovering its rich history. Your journey began in Fireheart Forest, then to Ironwood Forest where you learned from resilient spirits. In Wildwonder Forest, you discovered playful and curious spirits. At Grey Hills, you navigated the contentious land under Oiwa\'s watchful eye. Finally, at Deadwood Hillside, you honored Junko & Yukiko\'s legacy. Your dedication has honored Tsukimori\'s past. Well done! — Tenjiro Sensei', 'D', 1, NULL, 'event', '{\"reward\": {\"reward_exp\": 1000, \"reward_rank\": \"NONE\", \"reward_items\"